Today is the International Day for the Elimination of Violence Against Women. 

On Dec 6, 1989, 5:10 pm a misogynist POS entered Ecole Polytechnic in Montreal and killed 14 women. 

Since 1970, over 4,000 Indigenous women are missing or murdered.

Every 6 days, a woman in #Canada is killed by her intimate partner.

Violence against women hurts us all. We all need to do more in our own way everyday. 

Today we remember those 14 brave women and ALL WOMEN who were taken from us too soon by violence. Rest In Peace. 

Geneviève Bergeron

Hélène Colgan

Nathalie Croteau

Barbara Daigneault

Anne-Marie Edward

Maud Haviernick

Maryse Laganière

Maryse Leclair

Anne-Marie Lemay

Sonia Pelletier

Michèle Richard

Annie St-Arneault

Annie Turcotte

Barbara Klucznik-Widajewicz

#MontrealMassacre

👉🏼Don’t wing it or get lazy!! This is YOUR MOMEMT TO SHINE so you need to put in the work.YOU ❤️ ARE WORTH IT. 

👉🏼Practice also BUILDS YOUR CONFIDENCE. 🔥

👉🏼Practice will also help you develop and refine your idea so you talk has more impact and does better when it’s released on video on the Official TEDx YouTube Channel.
